12.30pm: South Africa win the toss and bat, they've included Janneman Malan and Kyle Verreynne for ODI debuts. Temba Bavuma is also fit to return, back in the No. 3 berth. Australia, meanwhile, have gone for something of a change-up in the middle order, with D'Arcy Short included as the spinning allrounder at No.7. That means no Ashton Agar, while Josh Hazlewood completes a Test-quality pace trio.

12.10pm: Morning all, welcome to unexclusively live 2D text coverage of the first ODI between South Africa and Australia - a series marooned at the end of the southern summer with little riding on it, bar bragging rights (of which there are always plenty in this fixture). South Africa have been further beset by injuries, and as Matt Roller writes in his preview, it has loaded the pressure on to Quinton de Kock, captain-keeper-opener in both white-ball formats. They are without a series win since March last year, and will have to go some if they are to end that barren run against a pretty much full-strength Australia.
